"Anyone can be Santa

118
00:07:07,027 --> 00:07:09,962
"Why can't a lady like me

119
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:14,601
"I admit, I'm underfed
but with a pillow from the bed

120
00:07:14,901 --> 00:07:17,131
"I could be Santa Claus

121
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:22,074
"Anyone can play Santa

122
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:25,172
"I fantasized it a lot

123
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:30,016
"With this hat upon my head
and his suit of Christmas red

124
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:33,376
"I could be Santa Claus

125
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:37,314
"And with his, 'ho, ho, ho' I'd be going

126
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:40,518
"Down the chimneys with his sack

127
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:45,489
"And although my curls may be showing

128
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:49,061
"I'll make sure they only see me
from the back

129
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:53,498
"Yes, anyone can be Santa

130
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:57,332
"A tantalizing remark

131
00:07:57,877 --> 00:08:01,905
"Though his boots are not my size
with a twinkle in my eyes

132
00:08:02,282 --> 00:08:05,047
"I could be Santa Claus

133
00:08:13,927 --> 00:08:17,522
"With his reindeer and his sleigh
I'd be up, up and away

134
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:20,292
"Yes, I could be Santa

135
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,266
"I could be Santa

136
00:08:22,469 --> 00:08:26,804
"I could be Santa Claus"

137
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,902
Santa, you changed your mind.

138
00:08:31,978 --> 00:08:33,946
Oh, joy! Oh, happy day!

139
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,215
Well, boys, what do you think?

140
00:08:38,585 --> 00:08:39,882
Hi, Mrs. C.

141
00:08:39,953 --> 00:08:41,853
Mrs. C!

142
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:44,522
No good, huh?

143
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:47,625
I guess we'll have to move
right on then to plan B.

144
00:08:47,827 --> 00:08:48,760
Plan B?

145
00:08:48,828 --> 00:08:49,761
What's that?

146
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:54,164
As I see it, Santa doesn't want to go
because nobody cares, right?

147
00:08:54,234 --> 00:08:54,962
Right.

148
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:58,562
He thinks there's no Christmas spirit,
no goodwill. Right?

149
00:08:58,838 --> 00:08:59,634
Right.

150
00:08:59,706 --> 00:09:03,836
So, all you have to do is go down there
and find some example...

151
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,538
...of Christmas spirit left over
from last year.

152
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:10,274
Scout up some goodwill
and show him some proof...

153
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:12,614
...that somebody cares. Right?

154
00:09:12,819 --> 00:09:13,650
Right.

155
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:17,788
Santa will change his mind,
and presto, Christmas is on again.

156
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:22,785
Now, make sure you don't get lost.

157
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:24,860
- Lost?
- Lost?

158
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:27,630
Vixen's made the trip. Haven't you, dear?

159
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:30,936
- She'll take you. No problem.
- Yeah, but...

160
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:35,103
Just hurry along and gather up
enough proof to change Santa's mind...

161
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,677
...and we can get on
with Christmas as usual.

162
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:42,781
Bon voyage. Send us a card now and then.

163
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:49,317
I wasn't sure I was doing the right thing.

164
00:09:49,389 --> 00:09:52,620
But faced with the idea of having
no Christmas at all...

165
00:09:52,959 --> 00:09:55,326
...drastic measures were called for.

166
00:09:57,864 --> 00:10:00,890
What's all that racket out there, Ma?

167
00:10:02,068 --> 00:10:06,005
It was just one of the reindeer
getting himself some exercise, dear.

168
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:09,802
With all the rest
and relaxation around here...

169
00:10:09,876 --> 00:10:12,174
...everybody's jumpy as a leapfrog.

170
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:15,506
It just isn't natural for this time of year.

171
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:19,982
They'll get used to it. I have already.

172
00:10:20,887 --> 00:10:24,448
I tell you, this is life.

173
00:10:24,924 --> 00:10:26,688
If you say so, dear.

174
00:10:27,227 --> 00:10:32,063
Are you thinking that I'm doing
the wrong thing by staying home?

175
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:36,429
Of course not, dear.
But if you should change your mind...

176
00:10:36,503 --> 00:10:39,905
Okay, what are you up to, Ma?

177
00:10:40,607 --> 00:10:42,371
Me? Up to something?

178
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:44,634
Ridiculous.

179
00:10:44,744 --> 00:10:46,644
Do I look like I'm up to something?

180
00:10:46,713 --> 00:10:49,546
No, you don't look like
you're up to something...

181
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:53,246
...but whenever you look like
you're not up to anything...

182
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,610
...you're up to something.

183
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:58,556
What are you up to, Ma?

184
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,492
It's nothing that need concern you.

185
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:03,494
Poor Jingle.

186
00:11:04,264 --> 00:11:05,459
Poor Jangle.

187
00:11:05,765 --> 00:11:07,699
Jingle! Jangle!

188
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:10,759
Concern it, Ma. What's going on?

189
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:13,037
They're only trying to help.

190
00:11:13,439 --> 00:11:14,998
Where are they?

191
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,701
They thought they'd just browse
around the world...

192
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:21,178
...and see if the folks didn't really care
about you and Christmas.

193
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:25,150
You mean, they went down there
out into that...

194
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:28,110
...cruel world by themselves?

195
00:11:28,288 --> 00:11:31,815
Of course not, silly.
Vixen went with them.

196
00:11:32,158 --> 00:11:36,026
Vixen! She's just a baby.

197
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:40,223
Poor little girl.

198
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:43,597
No telling what might happen.

199
00:11:44,137 --> 00:11:46,231
Now I'll have to go after them.

200
00:11:46,306 --> 00:11:49,503
Do you think you ought to, dear,
with your cold and all?

201
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:51,041
I have to go.

202
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:54,812
Those three won't even get
past the Miser brothers without...

203
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:57,009
The Miser brothers, oh dear!

204
00:11:57,784 --> 00:11:59,912
I forgot all about those two.

205
00:11:59,986 --> 00:12:02,614
Of all the fool things for them to do.

206
00:12:02,689 --> 00:12:06,683
If Snow Miser doesn't freeze them
just for the fun of it...

207
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:09,785
...his devil of a brother
will put the heat on them for sure.

208
00:12:11,497 --> 00:12:16,526
Dasher! On the double!

209
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:21,364
Away, Dasher! Away!

210
00:12:24,611 --> 00:12:27,046
<i>The Miser brothers. What a pair!</i>

211
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:30,840
<i>Snow Miser, who controls
the northern part of the world...</i>

212
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:33,147
<i>...trying to turn everything to icicles...</i>

213
00:12:33,219 --> 00:12:36,211
<i>...and his nasty brother
trying to keep the south so hot...</i>

214
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:38,314
<i>...with nary a snowflake a year.</i>

215
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:41,425
<i>Thanks to me, Vixen, Jingle and Jangle...</i>

216
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:43,757
<i>...were headed right between the two.</i>

217
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:46,195
Where are we? Where are we heading?

218
00:12:46,299 --> 00:12:47,960
What do you think?

219
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:52,598
Don't just stand there, you fools!

220
00:12:52,672 --> 00:12:55,300
They're part of the Santa Claus gang
of goody-goodies.

221
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:58,706
They must be on their way
to start everybody grieving...

222
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:00,439
...about white Christmas again.

223
00:13:01,314 --> 00:13:04,978
Don't let them get through.
Singe their britches for them.

224
00:13:07,053 --> 00:13:07,884
Get them.

225
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:10,048
Get them!

226
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:13,489
<i>Of course, I never dreamed
that little Vixen...</i>

227
00:13:13,559 --> 00:13:18,156
<i>...would make the mistake of flying
right smack into Heat Miser's territory.</i>

228
00:13:27,974 --> 00:13:31,035
They got away. They got away!

229
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:41,917
<i>Just a baby, perhaps,
but little Vixen pulled the boys...</i>

230
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:43,581
<i>...out of a pretty tight spot.</i>

231
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:45,624
I wonder where we are now?

232
00:13:45,692 --> 00:13:48,093
If you ask me, still in serious trouble.

233
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:49,896
Look! Look down there.

234
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,257
Southtown, U.S.A.

235
00:13:52,732 --> 00:13:56,066
That looks like as good a place as any
to find some Christmas spirit.

236
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,500
Take her down, Vixen old girl.

237
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,536
Where is everybody?

238
00:14:03,609 --> 00:14:05,509
Boy, that's what I'd like to know.

239
00:14:05,745 --> 00:14:09,773
How can we find any goodwill
if we can't even find any people?

240
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:14,149
All right, buddy, pull over.

241
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:15,743
What's the problem, Officer?

242
00:14:15,822 --> 00:14:18,757
"What's the problem?"
I'll tell you what the problem is.

243
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:20,824
Driving a... Riding a...

244
