I'll say they got in trouble.

272
00:15:44,977 --> 00:15:47,810
Wait until the judge gets finished
with them lawbreakers.

273
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,905
He'll give them what for.

274
00:15:51,184 --> 00:15:54,950
Not much Christmas spirit there,
and just as I feared...

275
00:15:55,588 --> 00:15:57,386
...they're in trouble already.

276
00:15:57,857 --> 00:16:00,189
We better find them quick.
Poor little guys.

277
00:16:00,893 --> 00:16:02,486
Must be scared to death.

278
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:06,294
I'm scared to death.

279
00:16:06,499 --> 00:16:10,527
Serves you right.
"Bark for the lady, Rover," indeed.

280
00:16:11,604 --> 00:16:14,369
Why don't we just skip the whole business
and go home?

281
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:17,636
I'd like to, but I hate to let Mrs. C down.

282
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:22,278
We've just got to find a trace of
Christmas spirit and goodwill somewhere.

283
00:16:22,548 --> 00:16:23,606
I know.

284
00:16:23,716 --> 00:16:27,050
Santa's favorites have always been
the little ones, the children.

285
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,984
Why don't we talk to one of them?

286
00:16:29,055 --> 00:16:30,284
Good idea.

287
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:33,960
